1
00:00:43,930 --> 00:00:47,094

2
00:01:53,354 --> 00:01:58,236

3
00:01:58,236 --> 00:02:01,017

What do you mean he's not the culprit?

4
00:02:01,017 --> 00:02:03,877
We clearly heard his confession!

5
00:02:10,433 --> 00:02:12,043
Yes, we did.

6
00:02:12,043 --> 00:02:15,293
Responses that didn't match the questions at all.

7
00:02:15,293 --> 00:02:19,833
What I asked him earlier was "why."

8
00:02:21,463 --> 00:02:22,803
 What is this?

9
00:02:22,803 --> 00:02:24,483
 Why did you hide this here?

10
00:02:24,483 --> 00:02:29,103
But out of nowhere, he answered that it was his.

11
00:02:29,103 --> 00:02:30,463
 This is mine.

12
00:02:30,463 --> 00:02:35,033
No matter how nervous he was, would anyone make a confession without

13
00:02:35,033 --> 00:02:38,213
trying to explain the item that was found in his own room?

14
00:02:38,213 --> 00:02:40,333
Even if he really did it himself.

15
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:41,483
Oh Bok's Dad!

16
00:02:41,483 --> 00:02:42,893
Let go of this!

17
00:02:42,893 --> 00:02:44,433
I'm going to kill that bastard!

18
00:02:44,433 --> 00:02:46,683
- Dad, you can't say things like that! 
 - What are you trying to do?

19
00:02:46,683 --> 00:02:48,083
Just let go of me!

20
00:02:48,083 --> 00:02:50,783
- I'll go and... 
 - Just a moment.

21
00:02:50,783 --> 00:02:52,883
What's going on?

22
00:02:52,883 --> 00:02:56,703
They say Detective Baek arrested his own nephew.

23
00:02:56,703 --> 00:02:57,973
That punk...

24
00:02:57,973 --> 00:02:59,513
That punk killed our sister...

25
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:00,753
Let go of me, both of you!

26
00:03:00,753 --> 00:03:03,323
- I'm going to tear his face apart! 
 - Geez!

27
00:03:03,323 --> 00:03:05,303
- Dad! 
 - Let go of this.

28
00:03:05,303 --> 00:03:07,933
- Let go! That punk... 
 - It's not him!

29
00:03:12,113 --> 00:03:13,803
It's not Hee Seop!

30
00:03:13,803 --> 00:03:16,203
It's definitely not him!

31
00:03:22,173 --> 00:03:24,003
This...

32
00:03:25,013 --> 00:03:27,053
Is this true?

33
00:03:28,045 --> 00:03:34,985

34
00:03:36,283 --> 00:03:38,103
How?

35
00:03:39,313 --> 00:03:40,743
How?

36
00:03:40,743 --> 00:03:42,743
Of all people...

37
00:03:42,743 --> 00:03:44,073
You?

38
00:03:44,073 --> 00:03:45,943
You!

39
00:03:47,273 --> 00:03:50,383
How can you kill a person, punk!

40
00:03:58,213 --> 00:04:00,113
What do you mean kill?

41
00:04:00,883 --> 00:04:01,833
What are you saying...

42
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:04,283
You can't back out of what you said now!

43
00:04:04,283 --> 00:04:08,043
All the evidence points to you, punk!

44
00:04:12,512 --> 00:04:14,883
 That matchbox.

45
00:04:14,883 --> 00:04:17,003
 And the note.

46
00:04:25,163 --> 00:04:27,213
 - Boo! 
 - Boo!

47
00:04:30,013 --> 00:04:33,773
 Wow, Hyung! What is all this?

48
00:04:34,523 --> 00:04:37,453
 Oh, it's nothing.

49
00:04:38,763 --> 00:04:40,643
 Looks like you need to clean up your room.

50
00:04:40,643 --> 00:04:42,793
 Come out for dinner.

51
00:04:46,963 --> 00:04:48,143
No...

52
00:04:48,143 --> 00:04:50,103
No, that's not it.

53
00:04:50,103 --> 00:04:51,713
It's not me!

54
00:04:51,713 --> 00:04:55,955
If it's not you, then what's all this?

55
00:04:55,955 --> 00:04:57,715
Huh?

56
00:04:59,223 --> 00:05:01,863
Whose blood is this?

57
00:05:21,193 --> 00:05:26,033
Last night, Hee Seop came by the house.

58
00:05:27,793 --> 00:05:32,513
Remember, he saved us yesterday at Motel Woojeong.

59
00:05:32,513 --> 00:05:34,723
Motel?

60
00:05:34,723 --> 00:05:37,213
He came because he was worried.

61
00:05:37,213 --> 00:05:40,113
When he's the one who got hurt.

62
00:05:42,073 --> 00:05:46,463
 My gosh! Look at these cuties!

63
00:05:46,463 --> 00:05:49,983
 - What? Are you guys dating? 
 - Excuse me?

64
00:05:50,603 --> 00:05:53,833
 Oh, dating? That would never happen!

65
00:05:54,453 --> 00:05:57,923
 I just thought she might've been very shaken up tonight.

66
00:05:57,923 --> 00:06:01,103
 I was worried about Soon Ae.

67
00:06:01,103 --> 00:06:02,833
 Yes.

68
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:06,523
 Hurry up and go.

69
00:06:06,523 --> 00:06:09,003
 You said you have someone to meet.

70
00:06:09,003 --> 00:06:10,633
 I'm going.

71
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:13,783
 Gosh, it's always the quiet ones.

72
00:06:15,623 --> 00:06:17,393
 Hey!

73
00:06:21,153 --> 00:06:24,113
 You better be good to my sister.

74
00:06:25,373 --> 00:06:30,653
 Don't go around fighting with this cute face! You got that?

75
00:06:30,653 --> 00:06:32,383
 Yes, I understand.

76
00:06:32,383 --> 00:06:34,133
 Good.

77
00:06:35,923 --> 00:06:38,223
 Why don't you get going?

78
00:06:38,983 --> 00:06:41,503
 - And come home early. 
 - Yes.

79
00:06:41,503 --> 00:06:44,753
 If you don't, I'll get in big trouble with Mom and Dad.

80
00:06:44,753 --> 00:06:46,653
 All right.

81
00:06:46,653 --> 00:06:50,133
 This sister will disappear for you.

82
00:06:50,133 --> 00:06:53,133
 Have a great time!

83
00:06:53,133 --> 00:06:55,013
 I'm off!

84
00:06:55,803 --> 00:06:56,943
 Come home early!

85
00:06:56,943 --> 00:06:59,283
 Yes, Miss!

86
00:07:01,293 --> 00:07:06,753
 Why is Lee Kyeong Ae... like that?

87
00:07:19,553 --> 00:07:21,773
 - Your wound... 
 - Whoa, yes.

88
00:07:21,773 --> 00:07:24,093
 Is it okay?

89
00:07:24,093 --> 00:07:25,823
 It's okay.

90
00:07:25,823 --> 00:07:29,993
 I can just put on some soybean paste later. 
  (Old wive's tale for healing wounds)

91
00:07:32,283 --> 00:07:36,343
 Since I saw that you're okay, I'll just get going, then.

92
00:07:38,763 --> 00:07:41,293
 We have a lot on our rooftop.

93
00:07:41,293 --> 00:07:43,163
 Soybean paste.

94
00:07:45,363 --> 00:07:46,763
Rooftop?

95
00:07:46,763 --> 00:07:48,183
Rooftop?

96
00:07:48,183 --> 00:07:50,343
Our rooftop?

97
00:07:51,153 --> 00:07:55,673
You were together at that time of night?

98
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:05,293
Exactly what time?

99
00:08:05,293 --> 00:08:08,543
And do you also remember how long you stayed together?

100
00:08:09,393 --> 00:08:11,203
Well...

101
00:08:11,203 --> 00:08:15,203
he said he would wait with me until Sister returned.

102
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:20,893
So he was with me all night until the sun came up.

103
00:08:20,893 --> 00:08:23,133
So there's no way Hee Seop could be the culprit—

104
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:27,873
What you just told us, does anyone else know?

105
00:08:30,353 --> 00:08:32,593
No.

106
00:08:32,593 --> 00:08:34,983
It should stay that way.

107
00:08:37,573 --> 00:08:41,073
From now on, forever.

108
00:08:41,073 --> 00:08:43,943
Then... what about Hee Seop?

109
00:08:43,943 --> 00:08:46,213
Who the hell cares about that punk Hee Seop?

110
00:08:46,213 --> 00:08:47,843
You haven't even known him for long!

111
00:08:47,843 --> 00:08:50,503
But you're calling a guy's name so affectionately!

112
00:08:50,503 --> 00:08:54,163
Don't you know what people are whispering about your sister?

113
00:08:54,163 --> 00:08:55,323
That night!

114
00:08:55,323 --> 00:08:59,093
Why would she have gone all the way to that abandoned house?

115
00:08:59,093 --> 00:09:02,993
She went to drink and meet guys!

116
00:09:02,993 --> 00:09:07,453
Don't you know that's what people are gossiping about her?

117
00:09:07,453 --> 00:09:13,203
What if they hear that the second daughter spent the entire night with a guy on her rooftop?

118
00:09:13,203 --> 00:09:19,333
Dirty rumors spread like wildfire in a small rural town like this!

119
00:09:19,333 --> 00:09:21,303
You!

120
00:09:21,303 --> 00:09:24,803
Must you have your mom hear that, too?

121
00:09:24,803 --> 00:09:25,933
Dad!

122
00:09:25,933 --> 00:09:30,143
If he's not guilty, he will be released.

123
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:35,453
So, none of you should

124
00:09:35,453 --> 00:09:40,863
never... utter that story.

125
00:09:47,643 --> 00:09:49,613
Mr. Yoon.

126
00:09:51,753 --> 00:09:53,943
I know it's shameless of me,

127
00:09:53,943 --> 00:09:58,873
but please, I am begging you.

128
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:18,835

129
00:10:19,843 --> 00:10:24,563
Man, he won't open his mouth! What a dumbass!

130
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:27,263
Hey!

131
00:10:27,263 --> 00:10:30,293
You got this blood splattered here while you were killing the victim. Right?

132
00:10:30,293 --> 00:10:35,403
When you cracked open Lee Kyeong Ae's head last night at that abandoned house!

133
00:10:35,403 --> 00:10:37,953
Answer me, punk!

134
00:10:37,953 --> 00:10:40,033
I'll do it.

135
00:10:41,053 --> 00:10:43,723
How could you do that? You're family.

136
00:10:43,723 --> 00:10:45,443
It will be heartbreaking.

137
00:10:45,443 --> 00:10:48,293
Besides, that's not even legal.

138
00:10:48,293 --> 00:10:51,363
Hey! Make him talk.

139
00:10:51,363 --> 00:10:53,613
- Yes. 
 - Yes.

140
00:10:54,803 --> 00:10:56,273
Hold him.

141
00:10:56,273 --> 00:10:57,723
Let's go.

142
00:10:57,723 --> 00:10:59,485
Come here.

143
00:10:59,485 --> 00:11:01,235
Punk!

144
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:10,713
While you were talking earlier, you said she was meeting someone. Right?

145
00:11:10,713 --> 00:11:13,433
When Kyeong Ae was leaving that night.

146
00:11:14,493 --> 00:11:16,513
Yes.

147
00:11:16,513 --> 00:11:20,963
But... she said he was really nice.

148
00:11:20,963 --> 00:11:25,233
She said he had saved her that day.

149
00:11:31,673 --> 00:11:33,833
 You already suspected who it was, didn't you?

150
00:11:33,833 --> 00:11:35,873
 If it wasn't the right confession,

151
00:11:35,873 --> 00:11:39,353
 there was only one reason why Baek Hee Seop would do that.

152
00:11:39,353 --> 00:11:43,993
 Of course, the person Dad wanted to protect was not Mom.

153
00:11:44,953 --> 00:11:46,133
 Are you hurt anywhere?

154
00:11:46,133 --> 00:11:50,443
 The last person Lee Kyeong Ae went to see that night.

155
00:11:50,443 --> 00:11:53,283
 Baek Yoo Seop, the one with the blue cap.

156
00:11:53,283 --> 00:11:56,813
 Once again, Dad was trying to protect his older brother

157
00:11:56,813 --> 00:11:59,703
 that he had been devoted to all his life.

158
00:12:03,023 --> 00:12:05,583
They asked about Hee Seop earlier, and now it's Yoo Seop?

159
00:12:05,583 --> 00:12:10,543
I'm really grateful that you saved our Yong Woo last time, Mr. Yoon.

160
00:12:10,543 --> 00:12:12,643
But why do you keep bothering our family?

161
00:12:12,643 --> 00:12:15,793
Don't you know there's a family who's suffering more than you right now in this town?

162
00:12:15,793 --> 00:12:19,733
Solving the case is my husband's job.

163
00:12:20,703 --> 00:12:23,543
It's because I have something I want to ask you personally.

164
00:12:23,543 --> 00:12:29,863
- You would have had to call anyway regarding Baek Hee Seop's news. 
 - If only I could see him.

165
00:12:29,863 --> 00:12:33,833
I heard it's been over three days since he was seen at the boarding house.

166
00:12:37,443 --> 00:12:39,443
This happens pretty often.

167
00:12:39,443 --> 00:12:42,203
Even though he's attending such a good university in Seoul,

168
00:12:42,203 --> 00:12:47,463
he's working at the factory from time to time to take his brother with him one day.

169
00:12:47,463 --> 00:12:49,093
 Uncle?

170
00:12:49,093 --> 00:12:52,093
He takes such good care of his younger brother.

171
00:12:52,093 --> 00:12:54,553
Even through all that,

172
00:12:54,553 --> 00:12:58,573
he comes down every weekend to see each other.

173
00:12:58,573 --> 00:13:03,063
So, would he even have time to sleep at the boarding house?

174
00:13:04,153 --> 00:13:06,933
Oh, gosh! My head hurts.

175
00:13:06,933 --> 00:13:10,843
Where is the boarding house located?

176
00:13:10,843 --> 00:13:12,423
They said it was near the school.

177
00:13:12,423 --> 00:13:15,733
They said somewhere in the Sillim neighborhood...

178
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:18,013
Sillim neighborhood?

179
00:13:20,693 --> 00:13:24,333
So, Uncle was a student at Seoul National University?

180
00:13:24,333 --> 00:13:26,303
Seoul National University...

181
00:13:26,303 --> 00:13:27,823
Third year in the Department of Korean Language and Literature.

182
00:13:27,823 --> 00:13:30,673
 We have a student teacher who will be with us for a month.

183
00:13:30,673 --> 00:13:32,403
 Ms. Lee Joo Young.

184
00:13:32,403 --> 00:13:37,493
 She is currently a senior at Seoul National University's Korean language and literature department.

185
00:13:37,493 --> 00:13:40,243
Same school. Same department.

186
00:13:42,423 --> 00:13:46,333
That means he had been in contact with the first victim.

187
00:13:47,343 --> 00:13:51,393
No one could have suspected anything since they all hid everything about him.

188
00:13:51,393 --> 00:13:55,293
Dad even got arrested in his place to protect his older brother.

189
00:13:55,293 --> 00:13:58,643
And Grandpa looked the other way because he feared the townspeople's gossip.

190
00:13:58,643 --> 00:14:02,913
Thanks to them, only Baek Yoo Seop was able to hide well.

191
00:14:02,913 --> 00:14:05,553
But even so,

192
00:14:06,483 --> 00:14:09,153
how come it was never even mentioned?

193
00:14:10,703 --> 00:14:12,413
It was mentioned.

194
00:14:12,413 --> 00:14:14,383
Very briefly.

195
00:14:14,383 --> 00:14:16,513
Once. As though in passing.

196
00:14:16,513 --> 00:14:19,243
 Stand up straight, punk!

197
00:14:20,423 --> 00:14:23,103
 Hey! Wake up! Hurry!

198
00:14:23,103 --> 00:14:24,893
 Just get up, okay?

199
00:14:24,893 --> 00:14:28,073
 Come on, I told you to stand up!

200
00:14:28,073 --> 00:14:31,113

201
00:14:31,113 --> 00:14:32,533
 Shit!

202
00:14:32,533 --> 00:14:33,903
 Come on, get up...

203
00:14:33,903 --> 00:14:36,403
 Come on, say something!

204
00:14:37,313 --> 00:14:38,473
Squad Chief!

205
00:14:38,473 --> 00:14:41,443
Officer Kim said he picked this up near that abandoned house.

206
00:14:41,443 --> 00:14:43,113
- Near the abandoned house? 
 - Yes.

207
00:14:43,113 --> 00:14:44,653
Should I submit it as a piece of evidence?

208
00:14:44,653 --> 00:14:46,583
What is this?

209
00:14:47,443 --> 00:14:49,433
Wow, it looks like a necklace.

210
00:14:49,433 --> 00:14:50,573
You try it on!

211
00:14:50,573 --> 00:14:53,173
Well, this can go over my head...

212
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:57,533
Hey!

213
00:15:01,563 --> 00:15:04,893
You said he confessed earlier.

214
00:15:09,083 --> 00:15:11,143
Hee Seop. Hee Seop!

215
00:15:11,143 --> 00:15:12,833
Are you all right?

216
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:14,663
Hee Seop.

217
00:15:20,623 --> 00:15:21,653
What's going on?

218
00:15:21,653 --> 00:15:23,773
Hey, Baek Dong Shik!

219
00:15:23,773 --> 00:15:25,733
What are you doing?

220
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:28,183
Hee Seop, wake up.

221
00:15:28,183 --> 00:15:29,323
This.

222
00:15:29,323 --> 00:15:30,833
This!

223
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:33,513
It's your brother's, right?

224
00:15:33,513 --> 00:15:35,693
It's Yoo Seop's, right?

225
00:15:35,693 --> 00:15:38,003
Tell me the truth, man!

226
00:15:38,673 --> 00:15:40,123
T-This is mine.

227
00:15:40,123 --> 00:15:42,663
Hey, look at this crazy idiot!

228
00:15:42,663 --> 00:15:45,453
He didn't speak when he took a beating. And now he's finally opening his mouth!

229
00:15:45,453 --> 00:15:49,633
I lent it for a short while, but it's been a while since I got it back.

230
00:15:49,633 --> 00:15:51,793
This was mine from the beginning.

231
00:15:51,793 --> 00:15:54,023
No, it's not Dad's.

232
00:15:56,813 --> 00:15:58,423
I'm sure of it.

233
00:15:58,423 --> 00:16:03,443
Ever since I was little, Uncle said it was his and wouldn't let me touch it.

234
00:16:05,313 --> 00:16:07,903
Baek Hee Seop will argue that it's his.

235
00:16:07,903 --> 00:16:10,203
They'll believe him, too.

236
00:16:10,203 --> 00:16:14,333
If things go according to how it was, he will be released no matter what.

237
00:16:14,333 --> 00:16:16,993
But because of his confession, we don't know what will happen this time.

238
00:16:16,993 --> 00:16:19,873
We have to find Baek Yoo Seop as soon as possible.

239
00:16:19,873 --> 00:16:23,123
So, we just have to find him?

240
00:16:23,123 --> 00:16:28,383
You said it would be difficult to prove the murderer with the necklace anyway.

241
00:16:28,383 --> 00:16:31,413
Since it's ambiguous as to when and where he dropped the necklace.

242
00:16:33,463 --> 00:16:36,443
That's why I'm going to look for one in advance.

243
00:16:37,103 --> 00:16:39,173
A piece of lost evidence.

244
00:16:43,363 --> 00:16:45,103
 That shirt from earlier

245
00:16:45,103 --> 00:16:49,193
 could've been a much more important piece of evidence.

246
00:16:53,273 --> 00:16:55,493
- Officer Kim! 
 - Goodness, Detective!

247
00:16:55,493 --> 00:16:57,173
Hello.

248
00:16:57,783 --> 00:16:59,783
- Your wife is doing well? 
 - Yes, of course.

249
00:16:59,783 --> 00:17:02,263
 During a time when forensic science was unfamiliar,

250
00:17:02,263 --> 00:17:04,873
 only if a small mistake...

251
00:17:19,203 --> 00:17:22,553
 hadn't ruined everything in an instant...

252
00:17:22,553 --> 00:17:24,693
Oh, geez!

253
00:17:25,663 --> 00:17:27,563
 Contaminated evidence.

254
00:17:27,563 --> 00:17:31,253
 As if it wasn't bad enough that they couldn't find any supporting evidence,

255
00:17:32,423 --> 00:17:36,203
 they totally lost it altogether once the investigation ended.

256
00:17:36,203 --> 00:17:40,993
 In a way, they even shattered all hopes for future possibilities.

257
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:48,793
 But this time will be different.

258
00:17:48,793 --> 00:17:50,363
 As long as we salvage that evidence,

259
00:17:50,363 --> 00:17:54,593
 Baek Yoo Seop won't be able to hide anywhere.

260
00:18:05,713 --> 00:18:08,563
It's dangerous to drive with something like this.

261
00:18:08,563 --> 00:18:10,403
What's going on?

262
00:18:11,163 --> 00:18:12,863
Oh, that's the one, isn't it?

263
00:18:12,863 --> 00:18:15,343
Detective Lee said he forgot to give you this.

264
00:18:15,343 --> 00:18:19,273
He said to place that in this bag since it's important.

265
00:18:19,273 --> 00:18:20,803
Yes.

266
00:18:34,783 --> 00:18:37,313
Drive safely.

